<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="408" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[813,1455,766,843]" pageId="5" pageNumber="408">
DISTRIBUTION. — Le genre 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1862" box="[1088,1180,766,790]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tettigidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="408" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1088,1180,766,790]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="408">Tettigidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
est largement réparti à travers les Amériques, depuis le Sud du 
<collectingCountry box="[1185,1261,793,817]" name="Canada" pageId="5" pageNumber="408">Canada</collectingCountry>
jusqu’au centre de l’Argentine (
<bibRefCitation author="Silva" box="[937,1093,819,843]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Silva" pageId="5" pageNumber="408" pagination="1 - 84" refId="ref12549" refString="SILVA D. S. M., CADENA- CASTANEDA O. J. &amp; PEREIRA M. R. 2021. - Batrachideinae (Orthoptera: Caelifera: Tetrigidae): an overview of the most diverse tetrigids of the Neotropical region. Zootaxa 4946 (1): 1 - 84. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4946.1.1" type="journal article" year="2021">
Silva 
<emphasis box="[989,1036,819,843]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="408">et al.</emphasis>
2021
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="408" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[811,1457,885,1485]" box="[813,943,885,911]" pageId="5" pageNumber="408">REMARQUES</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[811,1457,885,1485]" pageId="5" pageNumber="408">
Une première révision du genre 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1862" box="[1166,1267,917,943]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tettigidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="408" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1166,1267,917,943]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="408">Tettigidea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a été réalisée par 
<bibRefCitation author="Grant" box="[813,956,949,975]" firstAuthor="Grant" pageId="5" pageNumber="408" refId="ref11671" refString="GRANT H. J. 1962. - A revision of the subfamily Batrachideinae (Orthoptera; Tetrigidae). These, University of ColoradoColorado, 208 p." type="book" year="1962">Grant (1962)</bibRefCitation>
et faisait à l’époque ressortir 12 espèces valides. De nombreux taxons ont par la suite été décrits (
<bibRefCitation author="Podgornaya" firstAuthor="Podgornaya" pageId="5" pageNumber="408" pagination="200" refId="ref12200" refString="PODGORNAYA L. I. 1999. - A new species of the genus Tettigidea from Colombia (Orthoptera: Tetrigidae: Batrachideinae). Zoosystematica Rossica 8 (1): 200." type="journal article" year="1999">Podgornaya 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Gorochov &amp; Labandeira" box="[882,1210,1012,1039]" firstAuthor="Gorochov" pageId="5" pageNumber="408" pagination="357 - 370" refId="ref11596" refString="GOROCHOV A. V. &amp; LABANDEIRA C. C. 2012. - Eocene Orthoptera from Green River Formation of Wyoming (USA). Russian Entomological Journal 21 (4): 357 - 370." type="journal article" year="2012">Gorochov &amp; Labandeira 2012</bibRefCitation>
; Cadena-Castañeda &amp; Cardona 2015). Les 42 espèces désormais répertoriées ont récemment fait l’objet d’une révision pour aboutir à 20espèces valides scindées en cinq groupes: 
<emphasis box="[1158,1237,1108,1134]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="408">lateralis</emphasis>
(six espèces), 
<emphasis box="[1379,1453,1109,1134]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="408">armata</emphasis>
(trois espèces), 
<emphasis box="[975,1069,1141,1166]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="408">paratecta</emphasis>
(trois espèces), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1875" box="[1238,1335,1140,1166]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tettigidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="408" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cuspidata">
<emphasis box="[1238,1335,1140,1166]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="408">cuspidata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(quatre espèces) et 
<taxonomicName box="[912,996,1172,1198]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tettigidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="408" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scudderi">
<emphasis box="[912,996,1172,1198]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="408">scudderi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(quatre espèces) (
<bibRefCitation author="Silva" box="[1189,1361,1172,1198]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Silva" pageId="5" pageNumber="408" pagination="1 - 84" refId="ref12549" refString="SILVA D. S. M., CADENA- CASTANEDA O. J. &amp; PEREIRA M. R. 2021. - Batrachideinae (Orthoptera: Caelifera: Tetrigidae): an overview of the most diverse tetrigids of the Neotropical region. Zootaxa 4946 (1): 1 - 84. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4946.1.1" type="journal article" year="2021">
Silva 
<emphasis box="[1247,1298,1172,1198]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="408">et al.</emphasis>
2021
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[811,1457,885,1485]" pageId="5" pageNumber="408">
<taxonomicName box="[835,1064,1204,1230]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tettigidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="408" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multicostata">
<emphasis box="[835,1064,1204,1230]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="408">Tettigidea multicostata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="Bolivar" box="[1068,1210,1204,1230]" firstAuthor="Bolivar" pageId="5" pageNumber="408" pagination="175 - 313" refId="ref10790" refString="BOLIVAR I. 1887. - Essai sur les Acridiens de la tribu des Tettigidae. Annales de la Societe entomologique de Belgique 31: 175 - 313. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 12279407" type="journal article" year="1887">
<collectingRegion box="[1068,1145,1204,1230]" country="Venezuela" name="Bolivar" pageId="5" pageNumber="408">Bolívar</collectingRegion>
, 1887
</bibRefCitation>
a été mis en synonymie avec 
<taxonomicName authority="Scudder, 1875" authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1875" box="[863,1221,1235,1262]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tettigidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="408" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cuspidata">
<emphasis box="[863,1064,1236,1262]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="408">Tettigidea cuspidata</emphasis>
Scudder, 1875
</taxonomicName>
par 
<bibRefCitation author="Silva" box="[1266,1450,1236,1262]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Silva" pageId="5" pageNumber="408" pagination="1 - 84" refId="ref12549" refString="SILVA D. S. M., CADENA- CASTANEDA O. J. &amp; PEREIRA M. R. 2021. - Batrachideinae (Orthoptera: Caelifera: Tetrigidae): an overview of the most diverse tetrigids of the Neotropical region. Zootaxa 4946 (1): 1 - 84. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4946.1.1" type="journal article" year="2021">
Silva 
<emphasis box="[1322,1371,1236,1262]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="408">et al.</emphasis>
(2021)
</bibRefCitation>
. Cependant, d’après nos analyses, ce taxon semble valide puisqu’il présente un ovipositeur très différent (
<figureCitation box="[1331,1415,1299,1325]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="10.[133,144,1305,1323]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,216,1248]" captionTargetId="figure-310@10.[132,1455,216,1275]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIG. 6. — Comparaison des ovipositeurs des différentes espèces de Tettigidea du groupe cuspidata: A, T. cuspidata Scudder, 1875 (holotype); B, T. cuspidata (lectotype invalide de T. corrugata Bruner, 1910); C, T. cuspidata (lectotype de T. multicostata Bolívar, 1887); D, T. glabrata (holotype); E, T. claudei n. sp.; F, T. claudei n. sp. (allotype). Photos: ANSP, D. Silva et M. Pereira (A, B et D); MNCN, M. París (C); IRSNB, J. Lalanne (E); G. Doucet (F). Échelles: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6901683" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6901683/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="408">Fig. 6C</figureCitation>
) de celui de 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scudder" authorityYear="1875" box="[898,1018,1331,1357]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tettigidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="408" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cuspidata">
<emphasis box="[898,1018,1331,1357]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="408">T. cuspidata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(plus long chez ce dernier et avec des dents moins développées; 
<figureCitation box="[1028,1136,1363,1389]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="10.[133,144,1305,1323]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,216,1248]" captionTargetId="figure-310@10.[132,1455,216,1275]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIG. 6. — Comparaison des ovipositeurs des différentes espèces de Tettigidea du groupe cuspidata: A, T. cuspidata Scudder, 1875 (holotype); B, T. cuspidata (lectotype invalide de T. corrugata Bruner, 1910); C, T. cuspidata (lectotype de T. multicostata Bolívar, 1887); D, T. glabrata (holotype); E, T. claudei n. sp.; F, T. claudei n. sp. (allotype). Photos: ANSP, D. Silva et M. Pereira (A, B et D); MNCN, M. París (C); IRSNB, J. Lalanne (E); G. Doucet (F). Échelles: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6901683" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6901683/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="408">Fig. 6A, B</figureCitation>
) ainsi qu’un rapport DPT/LT plus petit (environ 1,2 pour le premier et supérieur à 1,5 pour le second). Nous proposons donc de rétablir 
<taxonomicName box="[1298,1453,1427,1453]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Tettigidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="408" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multicostata">
<emphasis box="[1298,1453,1427,1453]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="408">T. multicostata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="Bolivar" box="[813,958,1459,1485]" firstAuthor="Bolivar" pageId="5" pageNumber="408" pagination="175 - 313" refId="ref10790" refString="BOLIVAR I. 1887. - Essai sur les Acridiens de la tribu des Tettigidae. Annales de la Societe entomologique de Belgique 31: 175 - 313. https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 12279407" type="journal article" year="1887">
<collectingRegion box="[813,892,1459,1485]" country="Venezuela" name="Bolivar" pageId="5" pageNumber="408">Bolívar</collectingRegion>
, 1887
</bibRefCitation>
comme espèce valide.
</paragraph>
